title: Bonus 600 euro, la lavoratrice filma il sito Inps che apre le pagine di sconosciuti prima del blocco
description: Ecco la videodenuncia di una lavoratrice a partita Iva. Mentre inseriva i suoi dati nella sezione anagrafica della pagina Inps per fare domanda del bonus da 600 euro, le si aprivano le schede con nomi e cognomi e dati di assoluti sconosciuti che stavano presentando domanda. E che a sua volta conoscevano tutto di lei, a partire dalle sue difficoltà economiche. .  ."Questa è un raccoto arrivato con video - racconta l'avvocata bolognese Cathy La Torre -, ma ne abbiamo ricevute a centinaia per tutta la mattinata al telefono e via mail. Tantissimi ora vogliono denunciare al Garante della privacy la violazione dei dati personali. Il paradosso è che ora l'Inps rischia di dover pagare più soldi in risarcimento danni che nei bonus da 600 euro. Noi la segnalazione al Garante l'abbiamo fatta, nessuno vuole speculare su questa vicenda, ma è evidente che il sito va bloccato e aperto solo con garanzie diverse". .

Dean Schneider - Hakuna Mipaka VLOG 6
Meet the Animals of the Hakuna Mipaka Oasis - Dean Schneider

Since I live with much more animals together than only the Lions🦁 & the Monkeys🐒 I decided to introduce every single one of the Hakuna Mipaka Animals to you Guys personally 😍💪🏼

Each and everyone of them is my Family and there is nothing in this world i would not do in order to save their lifes and make sure they are happy and healthy 🤗

Support Hakuna Mipaka Oasis: https://www.deanschneider.com/donation/donate-now/
 
About Dean Schneider: 
I am a 27-year old Swiss guy, who dedicated his entire life to the animal world! Nowadays, I live in Africa, I am a member of a lion pride, my wife is a hyena and I’m a daddy of two monkeys. Besides that, I have built a global voice for our planet’s wildlife over the past two years!

Born in Switzerland (Zurich) on October 3, 1992, I was blessed to grow up in a loving family with my sister (one year older) and my parents, who were always very supportive and loving. My mother is originally from the Balkan region (Southeastern Europe), while my dad is a Swiss citizen. I discovered my deep passion for wildlife at the age of six or seven, through the legendary Steve Irwin! He was the one who brought wildlife into my living room in Zurich and inspired and educated me about all kinds of different animal species.

Even though I was so passionate about animals, I originally followed a very ordinary path to adulthood, eventually ending up in the finance industry as a financial advisor. After a very successful year, I decided to found my own company, which then, over the next three years, allowed me to generate the financial foundation to launch the Hakuna Mipaka project at the age of 23-24.

After starting my life in South Africa additional financial support form my Family allowed me to evolve and develop the Hakuna Mipaka Oasis for 2 Years without having to depend on any income sources such as offering touristic visits / programs, breeding or trading of animals, donations or any other monetary businesses! 

About Hakuna Mipaka:
The Hakuna Mipaka Oasis is located on around 400 hectares (four million square meters) in the wilderness of South Africa! It is home to thousands of different wild animal species! Besides that, the oasis also serves as a life-long home to a few rescued wild animals, which were born in captivity! We also do rehabilitation programs with different animals, which are then being released back into the wild.

The Hakuna Mipaka Oasis is my personal home and a private sanctuary that is NOT open to the public. We don’t cater to tourists and don’t allow any day visits or animal activities! We don’t breed animals and we are also not trading animals. I built this place for animals and not for humans. The Hakuna Mipaka oasis is a secure, wild & lifelong home to the animals that live here.

title: Coronavirus: colapsa sistema de salud en Ecuador
description:
Ecuador es uno de los países más afectados por el nuevo coronavirus, que cobra la vida de miles de personas alrededor del mundo. Espeluznantes vídeos difundidos en las redes sociales evidencia la dramática situación que se vive en el país vecino. Ciudadanos en Guayaquil denunciaron la aparición de cadáveres en las calles, como consecuencia del colapso sanitario que desencadenó la crisis por la pandemia del COVID-19, las autoridades de salud no levantaban los cuerpos en los domicilios.

El Gobierno de Ecuador reconoció las dificultades que se presentan para el levantamiento de cadáveres, por ello anunció una serie de medidas que establecen la construcción de cementerios para enterrar a los fallecidos por causas diferentes a coronavirus.

Durante una entrevista con el periodista ecuatoriano, Juan Carlos Aizprúa de Ecuavisa, se dio a conocer que 1616 personas están contagiadas de coronavirus en la provincia de Guayas, y en Guayaquil se registran 60 personas fallecidas, los familiares denuncian la lentitud de la red de salud pública.

Mientras que, las autoridades de la Policía Nacional en Ecuador señalaron que en los últimos 7 días se han retirado 308 cadáveres en los domicilios en la ciudad de Guayaquil, no todos los fallecidos son por coronavirus, también han fallecido personas en accidentes de tránsito, enfermedades crónicas, etc.

“Cuando la persona fallece en su domicilio, al cadáver hay que realizarle la prueba para descartar el COVID-19. Las autoridades sanitarias deben verificar la causa de la muerte, por lo que el proceso es más lento. En el caso de que los cuerpos den positivos para coronavirus y en la autopsia se revele que exista el virus inmediatamente el cuerpo debe ser cremado, para los otros fallecidos las autoridades están habilitando un espacio para crear un cementerio”, señaló el periodista Juan Carlos Aizprúa.
